<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand what draws buyers to Ferny Hills and what they expect when they arrive to inspect. Buyers searching here have often come from Keperra, where prices have risen, and they are comparing carefully across the corridor. Presentation standards matter because these are buyers who have been active in the market and will discount quickly for deferred maintenance or a property that does not match the lifestyle expectation the suburb sets.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The topography of Ferny Hills creates genuinely differentiated pockets within the suburb. Elevated blocks with north-facing aspects and bush outlook consistently attract the strongest buyer interest and command premiums over flat street-level lots. The Ferny Grove State High School catchment actively drives family-upgrader demand, and the suburb's position as a large-block alternative to Keperra means buyers who have been priced out of that suburb are a consistent and motivated part of the buyer pool.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
